docs.abstract: Malware was focused on networks used by Tribune Publishing, former owner of The Los Angeles Times. It was the first known attack on newspaper printing operations.
docs.snippet: Malware was focused on networks used by Tribune Publishing, former owner of The Los Angeles Times. It was the first known attack on newspaper printing operations.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Los Angeles Times says an unusual cyberattack that disrupted its printing operations and those at newspapers in San Diego and Florida over the weekend came from outside the United States, but it stopped short of accusing a specific foreign government.

headline.main: Cyberattack Disrupts Printing of Major Newspapers
headline.print_headline: Cyberattack In California Jams Papers On 2 Coasts

byline.original: By David E. Sanger and Nicole Perlroth

docs.abstract: Robert Lighthizer, the United States trade representative and a China skeptic, wants to prevent an anxious president from making a quick, empty deal in a rush to calm the markets.
docs.snippet: Robert Lighthizer, the United States trade representative and a China skeptic, wants to prevent an anxious president from making a quick, empty deal in a rush to calm the markets.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the middle of his crowded dinner in Buenos Aires with President Xi Jinping of China, President Trump leaned across the table, pointed to Robert Lighthizer, the United States trade representative whose skepticism of China runs deep, and declared, “That’s my negotiator!”

headline.main: As China Talks Begin, Trump’s Trade Negotiator Tries to Keep President From Wavering
headline.print_headline: Trump Asks Trade Warrior to Seek China Peace

docs.abstract: The chairmen of the House Judiciary and Oversight Committees urged Senate Republicans to pick up their inquiry into the F.B.I.’s investigations of the Trump campaign and Hillary Clinton’s emails.
docs.snippet: The chairmen of the House Judiciary and Oversight Committees urged Senate Republicans to pick up their inquiry into the F.B.I.’s investigations of the Trump campaign and Hillary Clinton’s emails.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In one of their final acts in the House majority, Republicans released a letter on Friday urging their Senate counterparts to pick up their politically charged inquiry into the handling of the F.B.I.’s investigations of President Trump’s campaign and Hillary Clinton’s use of a private email server, and called again for the appointment of a special counsel to study the matter.

headline.main: Departing House Republicans Try to Keep Investigation Into F.B.I. Alive
headline.print_headline: End of Sorts For Inquiry By G.O.P. In the House

docs.abstract: Ms. Omar, Democrat of Minnesota, says America is not the golden land she learned about as a Somali refugee. “I wasn’t comfortable with that hypocrisy.”
docs.snippet: Ms. Omar, Democrat of Minnesota, says America is not the golden land she learned about as a Somali refugee. “I wasn’t comfortable with that hypocrisy.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As a 12-year-old refugee from Somalia adjusting to life in the Virginia suburbs, Ilhan Omar fended off bullies who stuck gum on her scarf, knocked her down stairs and jumped her when she changed clothes for gym class.

headline.main: Glorified and Vilified, Representative-Elect Ilhan Omar Tells Critics: ‘Just Deal’
headline.print_headline: Glorified and Vilified, Former Somali Refugee Makes Her Way to Capitol

docs.abstract: The lawsuit by Richard Blumenthal, Mazie K. Hirono and Sheldon Whitehouse is the latest effort to get President Trump’s designation of Matthew G. Whitaker as acting attorney general declared unlawful.
docs.snippet: The lawsuit by Richard Blumenthal, Mazie K. Hirono and Sheldon Whitehouse is the latest effort to get President Trump’s designation of Matthew G. Whitaker as acting attorney general declared unlawful.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Three Democratic senators asked a Federal District Court judge on Monday to issue an injunction barring Matthew G. Whitaker from exercising the powers of head of the Justice Department, arguing that President Trump’s installation of Mr. Whitaker as acting attorney general violated the Constitution.

headline.main: Democratic Senators Challenge Whitaker Appointment in Court
headline.print_headline: Democratic Senators Go to Court to Challenge Acting Attorney General

docs.abstract: The Democrats who went public in a letter with their demand for new leadership hailed Nancy Pelosi as “a historic figure” but pledged “to change the status quo.”
docs.snippet: The Democrats who went public in a letter with their demand for new leadership hailed Nancy Pelosi as “a historic figure” but pledged “to change the status quo.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A rebellious group of 16 Democrats went public on Monday with their opposition to electing Representative Nancy Pelosi speaker when the new Congress convenes in January, taking the first formal step in a bid to force a leadership shake-up that could change the face of their party.

headline.main: ‘Message of Change’: 16 Rebel Democrats Vow to Oppose Pelosi
headline.print_headline: Whispers Become Salvos As 16 Rebels Buck Pelosi

docs.abstract: Among House Democrats, some strongly believe it is time for Nancy Pelosi to step aside for new leadership. But a serious challenger has yet to step forward.
docs.snippet: Among House Democrats, some strongly believe it is time for Nancy Pelosi to step aside for new leadership. But a serious challenger has yet to step forward.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — What if House Democrats tried to stage a coup and nobody showed up?

headline.main: If Not Pelosi, Who Should Lead? The Question Hovers Over a Simmering Rebellion
headline.print_headline: Democrats Who Oppose Pelosi  Also Resist a Run Against Her

docs.abstract: Representative Seth Moulton said that his efforts to deny Nancy Pelosi the speaker’s gavel were “bigger than her.” But nine more Democrats said they would not support her without rule changes.
docs.snippet: Representative Seth Moulton said that his efforts to deny Nancy Pelosi the speaker’s gavel were “bigger than her.” But nine more Democrats said they would not support her without rule changes.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The ringleader of a group of rebellious Democrats pushing to deny Representative Nancy Pelosi the speaker’s gavel in the new Congress appeared to soften his opposition on Monday, calling for negotiations in the clearest signal to date that Ms. Pelosi’s detractors have failed to thwart her steady march to the top post.

headline.main: Ringleader of Democratic Rebels Softens Tone on Pelosi
headline.print_headline: Leader of Rebellious Democrats Softens His Tone on Pelosi as Speaker

docs.abstract: In a complaint accusing the F.B.I. of discrimination, a dozen women described a pattern of instructors scrutinizing them more closely than men.
docs.snippet: In a complaint accusing the F.B.I. of discrimination, a dozen women described a pattern of instructors scrutinizing them more closely than men.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Danielle Snider was sailing through her training to be an F.B.I. agent last year, passing her fitness, academic and firearms tests. Then came the last phase: training on tactics like entering a house and confronting an armed attacker.

headline.main: F.B.I. Training Instructors Punish Women, Not Men, for Mistakes, Complaint Says
headline.print_headline: Lawsuit Says Instructors at the F.B.I. Gave Men an Edge, Despite Blunders

docs.abstract: The Supreme Court’s leader took offense at President Trump’s criticism of a federal judge, suggesting Mr. Trump had a profound misunderstanding of a judge’s role.
docs.snippet: The Supreme Court’s leader took offense at President Trump’s criticism of a federal judge, suggesting Mr. Trump had a profound misunderstanding of a judge’s role.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. defended the independence and integrity of the federal judiciary on Wednesday, rebuking President Trump for calling a judge who had ruled against his administration’s asylum policy “an Obama judge.”

headline.main: Chief Justice Defends Judicial Independence After Trump Attacks ‘Obama Judge’
headline.print_headline: Roberts Rebukes Trump for Swipe At ‘Obama Judge’
